BTW this change was done as a minimum change to get the functionality needed (minor extension of existing functionality). IMO a better API would change BQIO entirely as follows: BigQueryIO.Write takes input of type Foo, and a SerializableFunction that maps Foo -> TableRow. This would allow the table mapping to operate on Foo instead of TableRow. It would also better open the door for convenience mappers that could automatically generate a correct schema from Avro types and convert the Avro type to a TableRow. I refrained from implementing this earlier as it's a major backwards-incompatible change, and would probably engender a degree of bikeshedding. However it might be a better approach for BigQueryIO.Write in general, so worth bringing up.
